  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_15032641" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/15032641" />
    <a title="Elise Jensen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/740952-elise-jensen"><img alt="Elise Jensen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1289706029p2/740952.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/15032641?book_show_action=true">Feb 09, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elise Jensen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elise Jensen" href="/user/show/740952-elise-jensen">Elise Jensen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/740952-elise-jensen?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer15032641" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17433062176344071404">I actually quite enjoyed this book up until the very end, when I felt like the main female character just had some sort of weird personality seizure and did something that the character as you&apos;ve come to know her just wouldn&apos;t have done. It just made it seem poorly written to me, like Ms. Rice decided in the last 10 pages or so that it was going to have a sequel after all when she had been intending from the beginning for it to be a one-book story.</span>
  <span id="freeText17433062176344071404" style="display:none">I actually quite enjoyed this book up until the very end, when I felt like the main female character just had some sort of weird personality seizure and did something that the character as you've come to know her just wouldn't have done. It just made it seem poorly written to me, like Ms. Rice decided in the last 10 pages or so that it was going to have a sequel after all when she had been intending from the beginning for it to be a one-book story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17433062176344071404" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


